  "body": "\r\n#### System information\r\n\r\nGeth version: `1.8.18 and 1.8.19-unstable`\r\nOS & Version: Linux\r\n\r\n#### Expected behaviour\r\nGeth `personal.sendTransaction` works without error.\r\n\r\n#### Actual behaviour\r\nGeth got synced, but `sendTransaction` return `err=\"no suitable peer available\"`(In both stable and unstable version).\r\n\r\n#### Steps to reproduce the behaviour\r\n1- Run geth with light mode\r\n2- Use `personal.sendTransaction`\r\n\r\n",
